## Improvements Required

### 1. Fix the broken ARLogistic class (CRITICAL)

The `predict_proba` method currently returns a constant 0.5 array and has a `pass` statement inside the `if hasattr(self.model, 'classes_')` block. This means the AR baseline never produces real predictions and silently inflates KAN performance in comparisons. Additionally, `_make_lags` returns 3 values on the fail-safe path (line 77: `return X, y, np.ones(N)`) but only 2 values on the normal path, which will cause unpacking errors.

